lenders.name: Dr. Rich Day
lenders.occupational_info: In 2001 my son Eric was born.  Within a week he began crying almost non-stop.  He cried most of the day and most of the night and this went on for nearly 6 months. My wife and I weren't getting any sleep either.  We saw a pediatrician and neurologist, and none of them were able to help my son. A friend asked if we'd tried chiropractic.  "Chiropractic?",  I thought. "Why in the world would I take my child to a chiropractor? He doesn't have a bad back?".  We ended up taking Eric to a local chiropractor and within 2 weeks my son was sleeping through the night.  Around this same time I was laid off from my job, and my son's experience with chiropractic set my life on a course.  I went back to school at the University of Colorado for my pre-med courses and earned my Doctorate of Chiropractic in Kansas City. Today, my wife (who is also a chiropractor) and I devote ourselves to the health and wellness of, not just children, but entire families in our community.
